000C2A  1               ; [AI] These 274 bytes ($0C39-$0D4A) are Z-80 machine code, NOT 6502. After the
000C2A  1               ;      copy they reside in language-card RAM at $BC39 and are executed by the Z-80
000C2A  1               ;      CPU once CP/M is running -- they are the disk read/sector-translate glue the
000C2A  1               ;      Z-80 BIOS calls (entries SECTOR_MAP $BC39 and DISK_READ $BD25), operating on
000C2A  1               ;      the BIOS scratch at $FExx and the page-3 IOB mirror at $F3xx ($03xx as seen
000C2A  1               ;      by the 6502). Never executed by the 6502. Assembled by the Z-80 assembler
000C2A  1               ;      from CPM_BootLoader_DiskXlate.asm (ORG'd at its $BC39 run address) and
000C2A  1               ;      INCBIN'd here -- reassembles byte-identical to the original $0C39-$0D4A
000C2A  1               ;      bytes (the DISK_READ error-classify tail at $BD45-$BD4A is now part of the
000C2A  1               ;      routine, no longer a trailing .byte). The 6502 nibble-translate tables the
000C2A  1               ;      RWTS reads ($BD5A write table,
000C2A  1               ;      $BD04+$96.. read table) physically follow this region in the page image.
000C2A  1               CPM_READ_TRACKS_3:
