001000  1               ; LOAD_CPM  ($1000, runs in place) -- the real stage-2 entry
001000  1               ; ============================================================================
001000  1               ; [AI] Reached from the stage dispatcher once all 11 track-0 sectors are in. Bank in
001000  1               ;      LC RAM, clear this slot two current-track screen-holes, reset TEXT/video/kbd
001000  1               ;      and the stack. Recover the boot slot from X (X/16); the 44K 2.23 build requires
001000  1               ;      slot 6 -- any other slot prints MSG_SLOT_SIX and drops to the monitor.
001000  1               ; [DOC Vol1 1-3/1-4 ; facts sec.8.9] Apple CP/M's slot function assignments fix the
001000  1               ;      A:/B: disk controller in slot 6 and require it to be present, so cold boot must
001000  1               ;      come from the slot-6 controller -- the precondition this slot==6 check enforces.
001000  1               LOAD_CPM:
001000  1  AD 81 C0             LDA LC_ROM_BANK2_WR          ; $1000  AD 81 C0
001003  1  AD 81 C0             LDA LC_ROM_BANK2_WR          ; $1003  AD 81 C0
